{"id": 5240, "title": "Ticket #5240: collector crashes on RHEL7 when more than 1023 fds active", "description": "<blockquote>\nThe collector will SIGABRT on the cs pool's new RHEL7 machine when more than 1024 file descriptors are active.  The collector fails a compiler-generated assertion in FD_SET in selector.cpp, because we compile with -D_FORTIFY_SOURCE=2, and fortify \"knows\" that fd_sets can only have 1024 fd's in them, even though we go out of our way to malloc up larger fd_sets.\n\n<p>Technically, we're breaking the rules by not using fd_set explicitly, but this trick has works for many versions of unix.\n\n</p><p>For 8.2.10, I'll turn off -D_FORTIFY_SOURCE for selector.cpp only, and we'll need to think of a better solution for 8.4 or 8.5.  Going all the way to epoll would be nice, but a little disruptive for a stable series.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">\n<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=6061\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6061'); return false;\" title=\"fd_set bounds checking can cause abort in Selector class\">#6061</a></span></td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"center\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon ptr1\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\">\nfd_set bounds checking can cause abort in Selector class</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body><blockquote>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"../files/888/fd_set.patch\">fd_set.patch</a>\n3104 bytes added by jfrey on 2015-Aug-27 15:57:19 UTC.\n<br/>\nPatch to work around fortify's bounds check in FD_SET() and friends.<br/>\n</li></ul>\n</blockquote></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Aug-27 12:43</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/ac769236bb2911137066dd557561bab6733cd2bf\">[45732]</a></span>: copy edited versions of 8.2.10 version history items into the 8.3.8 version history: <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5219\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5219'); return false;\" title=\"Memory leak in ClassAd function split()\">#5219</a></span> <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5234\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5234'); return false;\" title=\"condor_vacate ignores other arguments when -constraint is passed.\">#5234</a></span> <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5236\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5236'); return false;\" title=\"Fix pslot preemption for user priority\">#5236</a></span> <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5240\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5240'); return false;\" title=\"collector crashes on RHEL7 when more than 1023 fds active\">#5240</a></span>  (By Karen Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Aug-26 16:33</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/910dab5ccc9d7d913877729f8180784f94b12f92\">[45706]</a></span>: Fix fedora warning with <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5240\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5240'); return false;\" title=\"collector crashes on RHEL7 when more than 1023 fds active\">#5240</a></span>  (By Greg Thain )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=